{"/service/ndnp/in/batch_in_janeway_ver01/data/sn87055779/00416150850/1930080101/0154.xml":{"full_text":"FEAR CANADIANS\nTO ERECT TARIFF\nWALL_FOR II. S.\nBennett Victory Expected\nto Curtail Import! to\nDominion.\nr\nBy OEOBGB B. BOLMM\nUf. S. Staff ComemM\nWASHINGTON, July 31. Til*\ndecisive victory iron by the conserva\ntives In the Canadian elections\nprobably spells trouble for American\nbusiness.\nThis to rather gloomily conceded\nhere today by those officials who\nkeep closdly In touch with Canadian\nconditions. Canada ,1a America\u2019s\ngreatest customer.\nThe new American tariff tow,\nthrowing up the highest barriers In\nhistory against Canadian products,\nwas the principal issue In the\nConservative-Liberal campaign across\nthe border. And the provinces dis\nplayed their resentment against It by\nturning out the government of\nMacKenzie King, who was accused of\nmaintaining a too complacent atti\ntude toward the new American law.\nOfficials Anxious\nAdministration officials are\nanxiously awaiting the formation of\nthe new Conservative government,\nheaded by Richard B. Bennett, and\nthe announcement of his policies.\nThat retaliatory tariff action Is to\nbe taken by the Bennett government\nagainst the United States is common\nly expected on all sides. The Con\nservative spokesmen pledged as much\nduring the campaign that preceded\nthe voting. Even the retaliation taken\nby the now defeated King govern\nment, effected through temporary\nlaws, was sot considered sufficient\nfor the Canadians. Evidently, by the\nsentiment expressed In their votes,\nthey want more drastic actum.\nThe effects on Canadlan-Amerlean\ntrade may well be very serious.\nCanada Is and has been for years\nAmerica\u2019s best customer. Almost\nevery year since the war $800,000,000\nworth of American products have\nflowed across the border, while about\nhalf as much, or $400,000,000, has\ncome from Canada to the United\nStates. The favorable trade balance\nin American favor is roughly $400,\n000,000 a year, and that has repre\nsented no inconsiderable factor In\nAmerican prosperity.\nFear Tariff War\nFrom the United States, Canada\nhas imported automobiles, machinery,\ngasoline and oil, Iron and steel prod\nucts and cotton. In return, the\nUnited States has taken cattle, dairy\nproducts, wheat, lumber, wood pulp\nand news print. The last named Is\nCanada\u2019s greatest export to the\nUnited States.\nIf Canada now proceeds under the\nnew government to erect higher tariff\nbarriers against American automo\nbiles, machinery, oil, iron and steel\nand cotton It will strike a serious\nblow at American business at the very\ntime when the scramble for world\nmarkets is becoming more and more\nacute.\nGreat Britain, which already has\nseme preferential treatment In\nCanada, Is launched upon a great\ncampaign for trading within the\nempire. Almost everytning that\nAmerica ships to Canada In great\nvolume must meet British products In\ncompetition.\nA new and retaliatory Canadian\ntariff system will not help American\nproducts In that competition. That\nmuch is assured. And administration\nofficials in Washington, scanning the\nhorizon for the return of prosperity\non this side of the border, do not\nview the prospect with much satis\nfaction.\nNEW CUBAN PARTY\nWINS RECOGNITION\nSy Cnltcd Frtta:\nHAVANA, Cuba, July 31. The\nlong fight of the Nationalist party,\nheaded by Carlos Mendietta, for for\nmal recognition and equal rights with\nthe other three parties of Cuba, ap\npeared to have been won today.\nPresident Gerardo Machado, in a\nmessage to congress today, recom\nmended that the party be officially\nrecognized and that it be given equal\nrights with the other parties In the\nNovember general elections.\nsaasaBcssssaBBaasHm\n*44\nROUND TRIP\nNEW\nYORK\nSimilar lou>fares to:\nWASHINGTON, D. C.\nPHILADELPHIA\nBALTIMORE\nATLANTIC CITY\nLONG ISLAND\n_ TICKETS on sale each Sat*\nurday to August 90, iuehistve.\nRETURN any time within\n30 days.\nSTOP-OVERS permitted\nat principal stations an route.\nWASHINGTON, D. C. at bo\nextra cost on all tickets to\nPhiladelphia and beyond*\nThese tickets good in citbsr\nPullman cars or coaches.\nAsk us about new low hn\ntickets to New York and\nBoston going one' direct\nroute, returning aaethw\nreturn limit 60 days;\nFor reservations and falls\nparticulars, consult' ticket\nagents.\nPennsylvania\nN Railroad\nW4n\nOUR BOARDING HOUSE\nBy Ahem\nori\u00bb come come, iMsr\n/WAV wrrtJ tHis xtvcffap\ntfoR3EpLAV*-~~ E&AP*\nI-fotP Vou rr 15 oMlV\nHOUSEBOAT WE AWES\n60<46 IS SPEldP OUR\nVAC/ttioM <*i \u2014AlffTT A\nlAftUSSrflP/ \u2014-I fr{A/E\nCrioSEAl *tW(S SIMPLE\nMARIAiE AfflKE AS\nbeFrfruifi mv post*\nA5 SKIPPER\nOF -THE\nf Sbil AH' ;ftsoM&eiUG MfAMP VoU deep\n[-TH\u2019 oMlv oM&s wrrH Ik A \"PiMaforb*\nBOAT-fc\u00a9* MAKES B JAILOR CiirfH A\nfH\u2019 RESI^F (35 LOOKHRictf BASS VOICE\nl\nUKE PICK-UPS OFF\nA life raft/\u2014\n~~Vll Be a \u00a9uesr;\nApmiral. O'F'Tft9\nttorffEAiroV MAv/V _\n\u2022ClKIAlS MV \\4tCATioU]\nulrfo CAM SIM6\n*0L\u2019 MAM RIVER'\nWriEM we <se*f\nSriUcKoU *tH*\nSAMP*\nii\n5=\u00a3!\nUDiawi\n,*SC'\nflM\u00ab3 A\n^is.<so/tr;\n\nN\nAUCTION BRIDGE\nBy MILTON C. WORK\nA WELL PLATED HAND\n\u2666A-Q-74\n5-4\n10-7-4\n\u26668-10*3-7\n\u26660*5 i N&rtW' J-M-3\nfW-J-Wfe g \u20220-1-2\n\u26665 (-Ml*-- VQ-J-3-8\n\u2666A-K44 1 \u00abqutw, J\u00bb|.3.2\n\u2666K-3-0-2\n\u20227*8\nA-K4-M\n\u2666J-5\nThe above hand was played in a\ngame of Contract. South bid one\nDiamond, West three hearts, North\npassed, and East bid four Hearts. Had\nWest bid only two Hearts, East might\nnot have felt strong enough to Jump.\nThe two-bid would have shown\nstrong Hearts, but would not have\nbeen a request for A'Jump with one\nprobable trick.\nIf the hand had been played at\nAuction, South would have bid one\nDiamond, West one Heart, North two\nDiamonds and after two passes. West;\nwould have obtained the contract with\na bid of two Hearts.\nWhen the hand was played, North\nstarted by leading the Ten of Dia\nmonds\u2014the top of three of hie part*\nner\u2019a suit. Dummy, 'with a four\nchette, covered with the Jack; and\nSouth won the trick. South then\nshifted to Spades and North apd\nSouth captured two Spade tricks. A\nthird Spade trick was ruffed by West\u2019s\nNine and then West led his Ace and\nJack of trumps, the latter overtaken\nby dummy\u2019s Queen. Dummy then led\nthe Queen of Diamonds and it was Im\nmaterial whether South covered or\nducked; as a matter of fact he cov\nered. West ruffed high and put dum\nmy in by leading the Trey of Hearts\nto dummy\u2019s Eight, so that dummy\ncould cash two Diamonds and give\nWest two important dub discards. In\nthis way game was ihade. If South\nhad not covered the second Diamond,\nWest would have discarded and East\nwould have led a third Diamond.\nThe play when pointed out seems\nto be simple, bnt many holders of the\nWest hand would have overlooked the\nchance of establishing and cashing\ndummy\u2019s Diamonds. In that case,\nafter ruffing the third Spade they\nwould have led four rounds of trumps\nand then would have attempted to\nmalm three Club tricks, although one\nClub trick lost would cost game. The\nrealization that dummy has two sure\nentries in trumps makes it easy to se\nlect the correct play.\n(Copyright John P. l>ille Co.)\nYOUNG APPROVES\nGLIDING SPORTS\nAeronautics Body Issues\nPamphlet on Air\nDevelopment.\nWASHINGTON, July 31-The Aero\nnautics Branch of the Department of\nCommerce is encouraging the develop\nment of gliding in the United Stales\nnot only as a sporting and recreation\nal activity but as a medium for fur\nthering interest in all phases of aero\nnautics, it is announced by Clarence\nM. Young, assistant secretary of com\nmerce for aeronautics.\nA phamplet covering many phrases\nof glider history and giving instruc\ntion information has just been Issued\nby the Aeronautics Branch.\n\u2018The glider movement is attracting\nthe attention of hundreds of persons,\u201d\nannounces Young. \u201cMany are in\nsearch of information concerning con\nstruction, operation and licensing of\ngliders. They also desire to know\nabout student permits and glider pilot\nlicenses. This Information is con\ntained in the new bulletin.\u201d\nHope and fear are Inseparable.\nThere is no hope without fear and no\nfear without hope.\n\u2014La Rochefoucauld.\nAnother lonesome vacation\n...teas*B.O.\u2019to blame?\n(Blit Odor)\nPEOPLE had been friendly enough at\nfirst\u2014invited him to go on picnics,\nwalks and rides. But not any more! Even\nhis own invitations were politely turned\ndown now. That\u2019s what always happened\n\u2014every year. He couldn\u2019t understand it.\nThen, returning to the city on a crowd\ned train, he overheard something. His\nown name and then\u2014\u201cB.O.\u201d And all at\nonce\u2014As lcnewl Realized why others left\nhim out of things, kept away from him.\nFor \u201cB.O.\u201d is the polite term for a con\ndition people dislike even to mention\u2014\nbody odor... Now he has adopted a sim\nple safeguard against this fault that kept\nhim unpopular. Next year won\u2019t see an\nother vacation ruined by \u201cB.O.\u201d\nnB. O\" woatkor\u2014beware!\nHot sultry days like these make us per\nspire more freely\u2014increase the danger of\n\u201cB.O.\u201d We quickly become need to this\never-present odor, seldom notice it in our\nselves\u2014only in others.\nBecause it is so easy to offend and not\nknow it, take this simple precaution.\nWash and bathe with lifebuoy. Then\nyou\u2019re safe. For Lifebudy, even in hard\nest water, gives an abundance of rich,\ncreamy, antiseptic lather that penetrates\npores\u2014removes all odor\u2014leaves yon\ngloriously dean and fresh. Its pleasant*\nextra-dean scent\u2014that vanishes as you\nrinse\u2014tells you lifebuoy purifies.\nKeeps complexions at their loveliest\nWhat a friend lifebuoy is to the com\nplexion! Millions of women know this.\nIts bland, searching lather deep-deansee\npores\u2014gently frees them of dogged im\npurities. Then watch dull slrinsTreshen\n\u2014healthy, radiant beauty return. Adopt\nlifebuoy today.\nLXVZK MQTHSU CO., CambriOf*. Mat*. \\\u2019f'A\n-V 1\nHEALTH SOAP\nps body otiar\u2014\n-V _ l\n.,l>SITIO>\n\n-4\ni;.\nr:jR -i. >-0.\nOF\nV>'.\n'r>\nPIUS\n:i>iv\n4 i:.\nwill\nthey\nIW\nTHE August Fur Sale presents authentic fur fashions you\nsee later in the season at prices guaranteed to be as low as\nOVV* IdWWi M1W C 7 V.\nwill be any time this year. Through the cooperation of a leading\nfurrier we are offering at the start of this sale an unusually large\ncollection of fur coats for sports, street and dress wear. This spe\ncial showing and the evident savings, together with the Robertson\nreputation for dependable furs should mean much to you.\nTHREE AUGUST SALE VALUE GROUPS:\n/f\nJ\nt\n115\n\n165\n\n195\nSELECT FROM:\nSealine Fur Coats\nMendoza Beaver Coats\nAmer. Opossum Coats\nSoft Lapin Fur Coats\nSupple Pony Fur Coats\nSELECT FROM:\nMuskrat Fur Coats\nSealine Fur Coats\nChinchilette Coats\nCivet Cat Coats\nMendoza Beaver Coats\nLapin Fur Coats\nSELECT FROM:\nHudson Seal Coats\nCaracul Fur Coats\nSilver Muskrat Coats\nSealine Muskrat Coats\nMendoza Beaver Coats\nr\n4\nV; -s\n,v,,'. V v-.\nI n\nr ?i i\nn\nMr. Wolter, An Expert Furrier, Will Be\nHere With a Large Stock of Fur Coats\nCoats made to your order\nand measurement without\nextra charge during this sale.\nFRIDA Y, August 1st\nSATURDAY, August 2nd\n-Jk\nTHROUGH the cooperation of Mr. Wolter, we are offering at the start of\nthis sale an unusually large collection of fur coats, made as cleverly as the\nlatest cloth coat from Paris. Many of these coats are more lustrously soft and\nsupple than ever before, with collars even more interesting. One sees the smart\nlarge bolster and cape shawl collars the sporty Johnny collars the chic\nhalf shawl collars, and scarf types Every coat represents a worth-while saving\nat its price.\nPrices, $97.50 to $625\n\u2018Vi <7 \u00abj\n.-'i1\nv:|Y-\nREGISTERED Fur Coats\n\u2014and what they mean to you\nEarly in the spring, the choicest pelts are hand\npicked from the manufacturer\u2019s stocks. They are\nregistered and used, exclusively, in the making of Fur\nCoats for Robertson Brothers Co.\nThis insures you the finest hand selected skins of\nthe entire season. With each Fur Coat a registered\ncertificate is given to the purchaser and a duplicate\nis kept on file in our office. Come in, let us tell you\nmore about these coats.\nFive Things\nto Remember\n2. The fur coats in\nthis side are auth\nentic 1930 31\nfashiorts.\n2. Made of winter\ntrapped skins...\nbest for their\nbeauty and serv\nI ice.\n8. All fur coat lin\nings are guaran\nteed for two sea\nson's wear.\nr4. A nominal de\nposit reserves\nyour selection.\n8. Free storage in\nour fur vault un\ntil November 1st.\n4","height":"32820","width":"24276"}}
